World Bank reports show that over one-third of household-run businesses closed down.Hospitality and tourism haven't fully recovered yet, while transporters have to deal with a curfew that delays deliveries. The vote by Parliament late last year to have the Covid-19 tax relief measures reversed makes it clear that the government has decided to have just a few Covid measures in place.
All these would have been all right were it not that the pandemic did not leave Kenya the way it found it.
According to the Kenya National Bureau of Statistics, 1.7 million Kenyans lost their jobs last year, while the economy contracted by 5.7 per cent.



