World Bank reports show that over one-third of household-run businesses closed down. Hospitality and tourism haven't fully recovered yet, while transporters have to deal with a curfew that delays deliveries.
So where is the economic recovery plan? Asking for prosperity and a thriving economy from the Jubilee government would be asking for too much, given that they have been unable to deliver for the past seven years.   Kenyans' lives have changed for the worse.



