It is time leaders talked to citizens to find out what they want. Before the pandemic, projects used to be stuffed down their throats: from laptops to railways and other grand projects that served to enrich a few while increasing the country's debt to astronomical levels. We have tasted the plans the government has for us and we do not wish to partake more of them.
 It's not like the pre-Covid times were good. The unemployment rate stood at 39 per cent according to the 2019 census results, the highest in the region.
But that was better than what we have now.  We are simply asking to be taken out of the fire back to the frying pan.
Where is the economic recovery plan for the losses we have undergone during the pandemic? Do they have any in the first place, or are we just sailing into an abyss?



